==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Erase
<hw>E*rase"</hw> <pr>(⟦esl⟧*r⟦amac⟧s")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Erased</conjf>
<pr>(⟦esl⟧*r⟦amac⟧st")</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>.
<conjf>Erasing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>erasus</ets>, p. p. of
<ets>eradere</ets> to erase; <ets>e</ets> out + <ets>radere</ets> to
scrape, scratch, shave. See <er>Rase</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
rub or scrape out, as letters or characters written, engraved, or
painted; to efface; to expunge; to cross out; <as>as, to <ex>erase</ex>
a word or a name</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fig.: To obliterate; to expunge; to blot out; --
used of ideas in the mind or memory.</def> <rj><au>Burke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Erased</ent>⟦br⟧
